# Rendering Engine

The VariantalX Rendering Engine (VXRender) is responsible for processing images, visual assets, custom renders, and runtime visual elements.

VXRender supports both built-in rendering systems and user-uploaded content.

---

## Supported Render Types

| Type          | Description               |
| ------------- | ------------------------- |
| Image         | Static image files        |
| Sprite        | Game and UI sprites       |
| Texture       | Surface textures          |
| RenderLayer   | Layered visual elements   |
| DynamicRender | Runtime-generated visuals |
| VariantRender | Variant-dependent visuals |

---

## Uploading Custom Images

Users may upload custom image assets.

```vx
render.upload<
    file="logo.png"
>;
```

Supported formats:

```text
.png
.jpg
.jpeg
.webp
.vxr
```

---

## Loading Images

Load an image into memory.

```vx
image = render.load<
    "background.png"
>;
```

---

## Displaying Images

Display a render on screen.

```vx
render.display<
    image
>;
```

---

## Render Layers

Render Layers control draw order.

```vx
layer Background = 0;
layer Interface = 5;
layer Overlay = 10;
```

Assign:

```vx
render.layer<
    image,
    Background
>;
```

---

## Dynamic Rendering

Generate visual content during runtime.

```vx
dynamicRender {

    width = 1920;
    height = 1080;

}
```

---

## Variant Rendering

Different variants may display different visual assets.

```vx
variant<1> {

    render.load<"classic_ui.png">;

}

variant<2> {

    render.load<"modern_ui.png">;

}
```

---

## Image Scaling

Resize images during rendering.

```vx
render.scale<
    image,
    width=500,
    height=500
>;
```

---

## Transparency

Control image transparency.

```vx
render.opacity<
    image,
    0.75
>;
```

---

## Runtime Asset Loading

Load assets while the application is running.

```vx
runtime.loadRender<
    "event_banner.png"
>;
```

---

## Custom Render Packages

Users may create render packages.

```vx
package HolidayTheme {

    include<
        "snow.png",
        "lights.png",
        "banner.png"
    >;

}
```

Load package:

```vx
render.package<
    HolidayTheme
>;
```

---

## Rendering Performance

Recommended limits:

```text
Maximum Image Size: 8192x8192
Maximum Render Layers: 128
Maximum Package Size: 500 MB
```

---

## Example

```vx
logo = render.load<
    "logo.png"
>;

render.scale<
    logo,
    width=250,
    height=250
>;

render.display<
    logo
>;
```

##

VXRender is available in VariantalX Runtime v2.3 and later.
